(72, 'en', 'E-MO10000LPD MINI Triton', 'Purpose: Reverse Osmosis Systems E-MO10000LPD MINI Triton series Ecosoft MO MINI &raquo;designed for demineralization of water for domestic and commercial use in suburban homes, cafes, restaurants, and small-scale industrial processes. Capacity: 0.5 cubic meters / hour Type of membrane element: Standard - Filmtec XLE 4040, Dow Chemical, USA Number of membrane elements: 2 Diameter connecting pipe: DN 25, DN 25 The system is a compact, functionally complete module. System equipment, instrumentation, piping, regulating valves are mounted on a metal frame. The process of demineralization is carried out on reverse osmosis membranes Filmtec elements manufactured by DOW Chemical (USA). During operation in the membrane module system separates water into two streams: demineralized water - and the permeate water with high salt content - concentrate. Part of the concentrate during the module is reset to the sewerage system, and part goes to the input of the high pressure pump, the so-called recycling of the concentrate. The system has an adjustable line of recycling, which allows to control and regulate the volume of discharge of the concentrate. Demineralized water (permeate) is fed into the collection (a set of system not included), which is mounted float switch, which disables the system when the maximum level. Automation system provides power to protect the pump from running dry, protect membranes from high blood pressure, provides activation and deactivation of the level in the collection of permeate, performs automatic hydraulic flushing of membranes. Periodically reverse osmosis membrane module requires chemical cleaning. Note: If necessary, the proposed model can be equipped with a dosing pump antiskalanta; controller with indication of the electrical conductivity of demineralized water. Consumables: Antiskalant (grade determined by analysis of source water).', '', 'E-MO10000LPD MINI Triton'),
